Ingredients.3: 2  fully cooked breaded chicken fillets (such as Kirkwood®)

Ingredients.5: 1 (8 ounce) package fresh mozzarella cheese, sliced

Ingredients.6: 1 tablespoon fresh basil, cut in very thin strips

Directions.1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 5 minutes.

Directions.2: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes.

Directions.3: Meanwhile, set 2 chicken fillets into the air fryer basket.

Directions.4: Air fry chicken fillets for 6 minutes. Flip fillets over and cook for 6 minutes on the other side. Spread marinara sauce over fillets. Top each fillet with mozzarella slices. Air fry until cheese is melted, about 3 more minutes.

Directions.5: Drain spaghetti noodles and divide noodles between 2 bowls. Carefully add a chicken fillet to each bowl. Garnish with basil.
